why do the tv licencing have to be so threatening and intimidating i have recently moved house already bought and paid for my tv licence at my previous address had a million things to do and get a really nasty threatenung letter from these despots because they think i have no licence they could learn a thing or to about good manners anyone else had similar it's not a question of 'duh phone them ' it's a question of being civil to your customers in answer to 'smells like a donkey' re b yes i just find the whole tone of these people high handed and rude their head of pr would not last a day in the private sector you should see the harassment you get if you tell them you haven't got a tv i moved into a student flat that had rooms each was technically a separate address so my flat mates had separate tv licences and i had no tv but the licence authority would not believe me and after months of threatening me with court they finally sent round a man who had the air of being ready to catch me red handed watching an unlicensed tv it was very funny to see his face drop when he realised i really didn't have a tv and guess what weeks later i got another letter threatening me with the bailiffs and ladywoodboy are you from birmingham b thats where i work Social rule Wheel of Fortune Poker jargon Shaggy dog story Singapore gay equality movement Ocean's Twelve Password I'm Sorry I Haven't a Clue Katelyn Faber SCO-Linux controversies James Bulger BBC Billboard Hot 100 Current teachings of Prem Rawat GNU General Public License Television licence Plame affair Cyprus dispute Big Brother (USA TV series) Vehicle registration plate British national identity card Sin City Stop Huntingdon Animal Cruelty Schapelle Corby Domestic violence Same-sex marriage in Canada Automatic number plate recognition EastEnders Leviathan (book) 2004 U.S. presidential election controversy, voting machines GED Thomas Hobbes Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Nintendo Entertainment System Have I Got 